HEADWORD: Chilostomata
<hw>Chi*lo*stom"a*ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ + <?/, <?/, outh.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An extensive suborder of marine Bryozoa, mostly with calcareous
shells. They have a movable lip and a lid to close the aperture of the
cells.</def> <altsp>[Also written <asp>Chillostomata</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

